relatedProfiles.full_name: Hania Aamir 哈尼亚·阿米尔
N A Y A N T H A R A

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It all started in grade 4 in primary school when I came last in the school gala because I couldn’t swim and it was compulsory to partake. I tried swimming that day and couldn’t get past the finish line and the kids in my class laughed and that trauma never left. Fast forward into adult hood when I had to turn down many underwater campaign shoots for not being able to swim. I went through life with this fear of swimming and it stayed with me. Years ago I saw a video of people having fun and jumping off boats in the Maldives and I knew it’s something I had to do. It was on! So I put my fear aside and set up swimming lessons and lo and behold this is when covid hit. The mere fact of being a 30 something adult taking swimming lessons with kids is in itself a nightmare as well but I was up for the challenge. Covid put a hold to the swimming lessons as it was impossible to swim in public pools at the time. 
After years and years of manifesting a trip to the Maldives it finally happened and I still didn’t know how to swim. 
This day we were on the boat and just finished snorkelling when Arjun’s cousins took off their life jackets and started diving into the ocean. I wasn’t going to let this opportunity pass! “I can’t swim but so what, if something happens they’re all here to save me!” I said
So I took my life jacket off and just jumped! YOLO!! 

This is a life changing moment for me. It may be a very basic thing for some of you but believe me I will cherish this moment for the rest of my life. To hear my friends and family cheering me on afterwards filled my eyes with tears of joy. I finally did it! I jumped into the Maldivian ocean! I want to scream it to the whole wide world! 🇲🇻♥️💕🧜‍♀️ 

Ps: thank you to the Bodango’s for believing in me and to the dive team at @tajmaldives for being so awesome.

When I heard that @browsbysuman was coming to India I knew I had to make a plan to visit the QUEEN OF EYEBROWS. I’m sharing the visit with you guys so you know exactly what to expect if you decide to go for microblading. 
I was super nervous at the beginning because it’s literally a tattoo on your face but Suman is so sweet and quickly put me at ease. Best part is that I don’t need to use eyebrow pencil to fill in any spots anymore! I’m so glad I got this done! @browsbysuman is here till the end of April for anyone who would like to get their brows looking fab 🥰

latestIgtvVideos.title: Combination Skin Routine
Mother’s Day gifting tips
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So it’s that time of the year.
Mother’s Day. 
We all love our Mom’s but some of us are really bad at gifting. 
Well never fear, Carla bhabhi is here. 
Here are a few gifting ideas for your queen. 
What kind of mom do you have?
Is she sporty, a foodie, feminine, glam, a yogi, or a beauty lover? 
Check my video for a few suggestions. 

If your mom likes feminine dresses, 
@malie.official is a fab brand to check out. 
For mom’s who love jewellery, my two favourite jewellery designers are 
@misho_designs and @outhousejewellery. 
For the mom on the move what a better way to gift her super chic mask chains from @tanned_official. 
For moms who love makeup why not gift a voucher from @sephora_india. 
@swiggyindia is a great destination to place an order for your moms favourite food you can eat with her on the day. 
@lemill is a lovely website for all things luxe if budget is absolutely not a problem for you. 
@houseofflowersbymarryme is an amazing flower boutique I adore and I’m a regular customer. I suggest getting flowers in addition to whatever you get your mom. 
@kosha_yoga_co is an amazing brand where you can find yoga mats and accessories if your mom is a yogi. 
And for moms who are fitness freaks - gifting her a subscription to an amazing fitness community like @sweat so she can get her fitness groove on during lockdown now that all the gyms are shut. 

If you’re worried that you don’t have any time, write to the brand and ask if they give gift vouchers so you can gift your mom and she can choose exactly what she wants ❤️ 

I hope this helps :)

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The folks at @theagelessclinic invited me to try their brand new Buccal Workout Facial. 
What is the Buccal Workout Facial? It’s a facial massage technique sometimes called the Inner Facial to contour the face naturally. They massage the face outside and also from the inside to relax the facial muscles and tone them creating a contouring effect.

latestPosts.caption: Thank you God for all the blessings of 2024. We welcomed the newest member of our family - Rosie and I came out of my shell. For those who don’t know - I accepted my hearing loss and I’m embracing it. I have only 25% hearing left but that’s not stopping me from reaching my full potential. Guys you can be whoever you want to be - just believe in yourself and remember the only barriers between you and your goal is YOU. Thank you to everyone who has supported me this year. My insta fam - I appreciate you! 2025 I’m ready for you! Lets go! ❤️
Merry Christmas from ours to yours. So happy to be spending the holidays with my parents this year. Heart so full. 🎄❤️
